definition.value: An acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of formic acid.
A glycosylglucose consisting of a beta-D-xylopyranose residue and a D-glucopyranose residue joined in sequence by a (1->3) glycosidic bond.
The S-geranoyl derivative of coenzyme A.
An omega-carboxyacyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with one of the carboxy groups of glutaric acid.
A glycosylgalactose consisting of a beta-D-glucopyranose residue and a beta-D-galactofuranose residue joined in sequence by a (1->2) glycosidic bond.
A long-chain fatty acyl-CoA resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of hexadecanoic acid with the thiol group of coenzyme A.
